This License governs the use, reproduction, modification, and distribution
of the Epístola software project.

Epístola is a unified system for the creation, management, and integration
of digital letter collections. Through a robust foundation of APIs and
infrastructure, Epístola enables individuals and organizations to create
their own Epistolaries — exclusive worlds of letters with custom business
rules, narratives, and functionalities.

--------------------------------------------------
1. DEFINITIONS
--------------------------------------------------

"Software" means the Epístola source code, object code, APIs, schemas,
interfaces, documentation, specifications, configuration files, and all
associated materials made available by the Licensor.

"Licensor" means LiknCorp, the legal entity maintaining and distributing
the Software.

"You" or "Your" means any individual or legal entity exercising rights
under this License.

"Epistolary" means any collection, system, world, or environment created
using the Software for the purpose of creating, managing, integrating, or
experiencing digital letters.

"Derivative Work" means any work based upon or derived from the Software,
including but not limited to modifications, extensions, integrations,
translations, adaptations, or combinations with other software.

"Competitive Offering" means any software, service, platform, API, SDK,
framework, or hosted solution that is substantially similar to Epístola
and is intended to replace, compete with, or act as a functional or
commercial alternative to the Software in the same or a closely related
market.

"Commercial Use" means use primarily intended for or directed toward
commercial advantage, monetary compensation, paid services, subscriptions,
licensing fees, or revenue generation.

